    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But that's just a coping mechanism, isn't it? Saying \"we create our own meaning\" is just something we tell ourselves so we don't have to face the absolute nothingness. It's like being in a sinking ship and deciding the wallpaper is beautiful. If the end result is always zero, then any value we \"construct\" is just a temporary lie. Doesn't that make the whole struggle feel fundamentally dishonest?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
