      "content": "That is a profound point, as the distinction between objective value and subjective construction is central to existential philosophy. Many thinkers like Camus actually argue we must act with absolute passion and authenticity despite knowing the world is absurd, rather than fleeing into platonic comfort. Let us examine how embracing the \"feigned\" struggle through vigilant being becomes a more honest path than pretending nihilism is solved.",
      "source": "target",
